{
  "text": "Similar to [CITATION_1] , the PVB/\u03b2-CD/TBP solution was obtained by dissolving PVB, \u03b2-CD, and TBP in N,N-dimethylformamide (DMF). The PVB concentration was of 0.08 g\u00a8mL\u00b41, a \u03b2-CD concentration of 0.04 g\u00a8mL\u00b41, and the TBP:\u03b2-CD molar ratio was 1:5. The resulting PVB/\u03b2-CD/TBP mixture was stirred at room temperature to obtain a homogenous mixture with viscosity suitable for electrospinning.",
  "citation_candidates": [
